description: Ride with DeadZone as he stalks a chemical distribution ring that is supplying processing chemicals used to create the drug Crank. Once square in his sights, DeadZone takes the ring’s warehouse by storm, but is soon retreating from the Crankers in their own building because he is so outmatched in the conflict…or is he? Find out in “More is Better!” Then, Deadzone storms a pimp-house where he is soon overwhelmed by a large group of heavily armed pimps. Later, Deadzone is bound and face front with a line-up of gunmen, about to get shot in the face where he has no protective armor. Is this the demise of Deadzone, or does the master-militant tactician have anything left to beat these impossible odds? At “Point Blank” range, Deadzone dares the pimps to shoot him in the face? Do they do it? Of course they do…but what happens next will amaze you!
name: Rage Machine: Take Two

description:
Demonslayer is the story of Jaclyn Hayes, an archaeologist from Boston whose trek to Tibet ended in disaster. Saved from certain death by a group of enigmatic monks who took her arrival as the fulfillment of an ancient prophecy, Jaclyn was trained to the limit in both mind and body and sent out into the world once again — as the Demonslayer!

The entire pre-Avatar Demonslayer saga is now available in one volume! Collected within are all six of the original Demonslayer issues that were published by Image comics as well as the ultra-rare issue #0 in one mammoth 160 page volume! The start of Marat Mychaels' breakout series is not to be missed, from her origin and boyfriend Michael getting turned into a demon, tot he breach of Hell itself, all the early defining moments of this series are now available in this trade paperback.

Originally published in (Image/Next) Demonslayer #0, vol 1 #1-3 and vol 2 (Into Hell) #1-3

Credits list a "colorist" but this trade paperback edition is presented in glorious greyscale.

Available in "regular" edition and limited edition white leather.

Five years from now, the DC Universe is reeling from a war with another Earth, leaving the world unprepared for an approaching evil that threatens to destroy the future. Can a time-traveling Batman Beyond help a massive cast of the DCU’s finest avert the impending apocalypse? Find out in this new weekly series that will forever alter the direction of The New 52!

Every ninety years, twelve gods incarnate as humans. They are loved. They are hated. In two years, they are dead. The team behind critically thermonuclear floor-fillers Young Avengers and PHONOGRAM reunite to start a new ongoing superhero fantasy with a beautiful oversized issue.
